Sum formula for the first n terms of geo.example_application:
Proving the sum formula for the first n terms of a geometric series: when q≠1, Sₙ = a₁(1 - qⁿ)/(1 - q)

 Step 1 (Base Case Verification): When n=1, the left side S₁ = a₁, the right side a₁(1 - q¹)/(1 - q) = a₁, holds true;
 Step 2 (Induction Hypothesis): Assume it holds for n=k, i.e., S_k = a₁(1 - qᵏ)/(1 - q);
 Step 3 (Induction Step): When n=k+1, S_{k+1} = S_k + a_{k+1} = [a₁(1 - qᵏ)/(1 - q)] + a₁qᵏ
 = [a₁(1 - qᵏ) + a₁qᵏ(1 - q)] / (1 - q)
 = [a₁(1 - qᵏ + qᵏ - q^{k+1})] / (1 - q)
 = a₁(1 - q^{k+1})/(1 - q), the equation holds;
 Step 4 (Conclusion Integration): By mathematical induction, the formula holds for all n∈N*.

